OL,3,CSex offender who abducted and abused
OL,4,Cgirl has sentence appeal rejected
OL,6,F"Nothing I say should be considered to
OL,7,Fbe minimising the offence. Clearly a
OL,8,Fsubstantial sentence was appropriate."
OL,10,FShe said Miller lived as a woman "for
OL,11,Fmany years", and his "transgender
OL,12,Fidentity had been a factor throughout
OL,13,Fhis life".
OL,15,FShe added: "Too much weight has been
OL,16,Fattached to that factor. It is clear
OL,17,Fthe appellant has experienced
OL,18,Fpsychological difficulties throughout
OL,19,Fhis life. This is his first offence
OL,20,Ffor such a serious matter.
