OL,6,FThey added: "By the time of the
OL,7,Fincident, the appellant was already
OL,8,Fdressing as a woman as a matter of
OL,9,Froutine, rather than for any more
OL,10,Fsinister a reason."
OL,12,FIn a written judgment, Lord Carloway
OL,13,Fsaid the court could not rule Miller's
OL,14,Fsentence as "excessive", stating that
OL,15,Fthe court took into account the
OL,16,F"extreme depravity" of his crimes.
